European, wide range in Europe (
Chandler 2004
). Rather common in herb-rich forests in South Finland, no former records from Finnish Lapland.

Immature stages are unknown, but adults have been reared from moss patches and exposed forest soil in Norway (
Okland 1999
) and from an aspen log bearing polypores (J. Jakovlev, unpublished). However, due to the methods used (eclector trap in situ), it can not be ruled out that adult specimens were already present in the substrate when the trap was set (
Okland 1999
). Congeneric species G. apicalis Meigen, 1818 has been reared from moss cushions around a seepage in Germany ( Lenz 1927 ).
